The '''''Symphony in D Major, Op. 3, No. 2''''' is a Mannheim symphony by [[Johann Stamitz]], written sometime from 1750 to 1754.<ref>{{cite web|title=Notes to Johann Stamitz Symphonies Vol. 1 on Naxos|url=http://www.naxos.com/mainsite/blurbs_reviews.asp?item_code=8.553294&catNum=553194&filetype=About%20this%20Recording&language=English#|accessdate=19 September 2009}}</ref> It has a 4-movement symphonic scheme: #Presto #Andantino #Menuetto #Prestissimo This symphony, just like the others by Stamitz, definitely influenced [[Joseph Haydn]] and [[Mozart]].{{Citation needed|date=January 2014}} It is about 10 minutes long.
